

PyTTP - a small and dirty WSGI-compliant server written entirely in Python


File Structure
==============
pyttp/core.py: HTTP Requests and Responses
pyttp/cnetwork.py: Simple socket listener; including SSL support
pyttp/cwsgi.py: WSGI-wrapper for network.py
pyttp/database.py: database abstraction - might be slow as hell;
             used as a means to teach me some meta-programming
pyttp/chtml.py: write HTML directly in Python; who needs templates anyways?
pyttp/clogger.py: names says it all
pyttp/chelpers.py: some helpers for parsing and uploading
pyttp/cplugin.py: base class for a plugin mechanism
pyttp/ctimeout.py: helper for dealing with potential deadlocks
pyttp/cconfig.py: ugly brother to ConfigParser
exmaples/: some example WSGI-apps; will only run if pyttp module is in path
